cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces two temporal logics and discusses their decidability and complexity. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the behaviour of reactive systems and introduces a logic for specifying requirements. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of temporal logics for specifying properties of systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper introduces a logic for specifying context-free requirements. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the behaviour of real-time systems and introduces a logic for specifying requirements.
